{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"54f3bdfa-8a1d-4a7b-bc1b-7995c3c73ba3","content":"The working directory is empty, so I'll provide guidance based on standard MCP skill evaluation practices.\n\n## Evaluation Format\n\nEvaluations are typically defined in an **`evaluation.yml`** file with this structure:\n\n```yaml\nquestions:\n  - text: \"Find all products under $50 in the electronics category\"\n    expectations:\n      - kind: tool_call\n        tool: search_products\n        arguments:\n          category: \"electronics\"\n          max_price: 50\n      - kind: response_includes\n        value: # expected product names or key facts\n\n  - text: \"What's the price difference between Product A and Product B?\"\n    expectations:\n      - kind: tool_call\n        tool: get_product_details\n        # Called at least twice\n      - kind: response_includes\n        value: \"$15\"  # the actual difference\n```\n\n## What Makes a Good Evaluation Question\n\n| Quality | Example |\n|---------|---------|\n| **Tests tool selection** | \"Which products are on sale?\" → should pick `get_promotions`, not `search_products` |\n| **Tests parameter extraction** | \"Show me red shoes size 10\" → correct filters passed |\n| **Tests multi-step reasoning** | \"Is Product A cheaper than the average in its category?\" → requires multiple calls + math |\n| **Tests error handling** | \"Find SKU XYZ-000\" → graceful handling of not-found |\n| **Has a verifiable answer** | Questions with concrete, deterministic expected outputs |\n\n## Tips\n\n1. **Cover single-tool and multi-tool scenarios** — simple lookups plus compositions.\n2. **Include ambiguous queries** — tests whether the LLM asks for clarification or makes reasonable defaults.\n3. **Pin test data** — evaluations should run against a fixed catalog snapshot so answers are deterministic.\n4. **Use `response_includes`** for factual correctness and `tool_call` expectations for behavioral correctness.\n\nWould you like me t